<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173484>
    bibo:endPage "50" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "31" ;
    bibo:volume "1285" ;
    dc:creator "Shelley, Rowland M.; Medrano, Michael F." ;
    dc:date "2006" ;
    dc:title "Nesoressa crawfordi, n. gen., n. sp., a montane island milliped in New Mexico, USA; proposal of the new tribe Nesoressini and a preliminary cladogram of the lineage \" Aniulina \" (Julida: Parajulidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173485>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173489>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173490>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173487> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173485>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Nesoressa crawfordi. Head and pleurotergites 1 – 9 of a male paratype, setation omitted. Scale line = 1. 0 0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/173485/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173489>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13 – 19. Gonopodal features of male paratype of N. crawfordi. 13, segment 7, lateral view of left side. 14, the same, ventral view. 15, anterior gonopods, anterior view. 16, the same, caudal view. 17, posterior gonopods, anterior view. 18, the same, lateral view of left side, prostatic groove omitted on stem of solenomere to simplify the drawing; the labeled process \" C \" is that on the right telopodite. 19, right posterior gonopod, caudal view. ACL, anterior gonopod coxal lobe; C, posterior gonopod telopodal process \" C \"; CO, coxa; PCL, posterior gonopod coxal lobe; PFP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere; ST, sternum; T, anterior gonopod telopodite. Scale line = 0.25 mm for figs. 15 – 19, 2. 4 mm for figs. 13 – 14." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/173489/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173490>
    dc:description "FIGURES 20 – 22. Cyphopodal features of female paratype of N. crawfordi. 20, cyphopodal aperture and cyphopods in situ, ventral view. 21, cyphopods, dorsal view. 22, the same / synoperculum, ventral view. SO, synoperculum; V, valve. Scale line = 0. 42 mm for fig. 20, 0. 50 mm for figs. 21 – 22." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/173490/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.173487>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution of the clade \" Aniulina. \" 1, Aniulini; 2, Gosiulini; 3, Parajulini; dots, Nesoressini. The dashed line denotes the uncertain boundary of both Aniulini and \" Aniulina \" through Manitoba and western & central Ontario." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/173487/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

